# Generation 4: a ground knowledge base — assert facts, query under
# the closed-world assumption.
# Unknown before being told (closed-world: absent => false).
> is socrates a man?
< No.
# Teach a fact; it echoes the learned Prolog term.
> socrates is a man
< Learned: man(socrates).
> is socrates a man?
< Yes.
# "an" article works too.
> bob is an animal
< Learned: animal(bob).
> is bob an animal?
< Yes.
# Facts don't leak across predicates/subjects.
> is bob a man?
< No.
> is socrates an animal?
< No.
# Non-knowledge turns still behave; unparseable input -> honest admission.
> hello
< Hi there!
> the quick brown fox
< I don't understand that yet.
